## Start locally

Requirements: Node.js 24 LTS or later, pnpm through Corepack, and Docker.

```bash
pnpm setup
pnpm dev
```

Open `http://localhost:5173` and sign in with the development credentials printed by setup. The production server uses `PORT` (default 3000) and serves the API and SPA together.

## Quality and database commands

```bash
pnpm doctor
pnpm check
pnpm verify
pnpm db:generate
pnpm db:migrate
pnpm db:studio
pnpm db:seed
pnpm db:reset
pnpm deploy:check
```

`pnpm verify` is the required pre-deployment gate. It runs linting, strict types, tests, dead-code detection, a production build, browser tests, and a production-server smoke test. `db:reset` refuses to run in production. Seeds are never automatic in production.

Read `OWNER_GUIDE.md` for operations, `AGENTS.md` before agent-assisted work, `docs/QUALITY.md` for the quality gate, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for boundaries, `docs/SECRETS.md` for 1Password, and `docs/RAILWAY.md` to deploy.

## Included product shell

Authentication, profiles, resumable onboarding, personas, role-based authorization, personal/team workspaces, invitations, responsive shell/navigation, settings, support tickets, safe administration, audit events, billing/AI/email/storage scaffolding, and Docker/Railway deployment are included. Optional providers remain honest and non-blocking when unconfigured.

## Provenance

The visual foundation derives from `knowsuchagency/cloudflare-template`; its Nothing, Apex, and Onyx systems and upstream notices are preserved. See `docs/UPSTREAM.md`.
